vectorData.altText: 8. Cerebral arteries and veins are located in the ______________ space.
That’s right!  The subarachnoid space contains the cerebral arteries and veins.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

The relationships of the arachnoid mater, subarachnoid space and the pia mater in the cranium are the same as the spinal meninges: the arachnoid and pia mater are separated by the subarachnoid space, which contains CSF. The hydrostatic pressure of the CSF holds the arachnoid mater against the dura mater. The delicate pia mater is closely adhered to the surface of the brain, and cannot be separated from it, nor discerned with the naked eye.

The subarachnoid space contains the cerebral arteries and veins. A bleed in this space is a subarachnoid hemorrhage, and usually is the result of the tearing or rupture of cerebral arteries. Because arterial blood is under pressure, a subarachnoid hemorrhage usually develops very rapidly.
